<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFCFFDDA5CDFE431A60FD15" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFCFFDDA5CDFE431C39FE75" blockId="12.[136,518,410,437]" box="[136,518,410,437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFFCFFDDA5CDFE431C39FE75" box="[136,518,410,437]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="4">
6. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA5E1FE421C3EFE75" authority="Linnaeus (1753: 626)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1753" box="[164,513,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA5E1FE421F39FE75" bold="true" box="[164,262,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lantana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA448FE431C3EFE75" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[269,513,410,437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 1200" refId="ref35181" refString="Linnaeus, C. von (1753) Species Plantarum. L. Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 1 - 1200." type="book chapter" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 626)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFCFFDDA5CDFE3B1A60FD15" blockId="12.[136,1452,482,1120]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Subshrubs, shrubs or treelets, monoecious, branches with ou without prickles, often aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences axillary, simple, racemes capituliform, multiflorous, compact, rachis elongated or not in fructification; bracts spirally arranged, chartaceous, green or vinaceous; bracteoles absent. Flowers sessile; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, truncate or 2-lobed, each lobe rare 2-toothed, accrescent or not in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed, 2-labiate; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair without connective appendages, thecae parallel; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma oblique. Fruit a drupe, with 1 pyrene, brown, purple or black, external surface smooth or rugose.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFCFFDDA5F8FD061EEEFBA0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFCFFDDA5F8FD061CF1FC49" blockId="12.[136,1452,482,1120]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA5F8FD061F25FD38" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[189,282,735,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA5F8FD061F25FD38" box="[189,282,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lantana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA4BEFD061D75FD38" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[507,842,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Lantaneae">
Lantaneae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA73AFD071D7CFD38" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[639,835,734,760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA783FD061D3FFD38" box="[710,768,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and has approximately 100 species distributed in the Neotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA431FCDB1C2EFCDC" author="Rotman, A. D." box="[372,529,770,796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="297 - 301" refId="ref37862" refString="Rotman, A. D. (2009) El genero Lantana L. (Verbenaceae - Verbenoideae) en Paraguay: sinopsis y novedades. Candollea 64: 297 - 301." type="journal article" year="2009">Rotman 2009</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA7C4FCDA1D1FFCDC" box="[641,800,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by the capituliform racemes, corolla 2-labiate, and fruit a drupe with 1 pyrene. There are approximately 30 species in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFFCFFDDA11AFCFF1A9CFC80" box="[1119,1187,806,832]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA1F4FCFF1BA0FC81" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Menini Neto, L. &amp; Cabral, A. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[1201,1439,806,833]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="191 - 196" refId="ref33759" refString="Cardoso, P. H., Menini Neto, L., Cabral, A. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2019 b) Lantana caudata (Verbenaceae), a new species from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Phytotaxa 424: 191 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 424.3.7" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA052FCFE1B70FC80" box="[1303,1359,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2019b
</bibRefCitation>
), and the Atlantic Forest is the richest phytogeographic domain. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA603FC921D9CFCA4" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[838,931,843,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA603FC921D9CFCA4" box="[838,931,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lantana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by 10 species in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFFCFFDDA040FC931B97FCA4" box="[1285,1448,842,868]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, and is the richest genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA4F7FCB71C00FC48" authorityName="J. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1805" box="[434,575,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
in this state.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFCFFDDA5F8FC4A1EEEFBA0" blockId="12.[136,1452,482,1120]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA5F8FC4A1F25FC6C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[189,282,915,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA5F8FC4A1F25FC6C" box="[189,282,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lantana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA734FC4A1C85FC6C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[625,698,915,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA734FC4A1C85FC6C" box="[625,698,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lippia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it can be very difficult to differentiate them. The morphology of the fruit is the only reliable character used in the delimitation of both genera: the species presenting aschizocarp fruit with 2 cluses or a drupe with 2 pyrenes are considered part of 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA636FC021DFCFC34" box="[883,963,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA636FC021D80FC34" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[883,959,987,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Lippia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
while the species presenting a drupe with 1 pyrene belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA40DFC261CFCFBD8" authority="(Silva &amp; Salimena 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Silva &amp; Salimena" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[328,707,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA40DFC261F9AFBD8" box="[328,421,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lantana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA4F6FC271C84FBD8" author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[435,699,1022,1048]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="57 - 59" refId="ref39160" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2002) Novas combinacoes e novos sinonimos em Lippia e Lantana (Verbenaceae). Darwiniana 40: 57 - 59." type="journal article" year="2002">Silva &amp; Salimena 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, phylogenetic analyses indicated that both genera are not monophyletic and must be recircumscribed in only one genus or fragmented in several genera (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA1EBFBFB1EFAFBA0" author="Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Olmstead, R. G." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="103 - 119" refId="ref35369" refString="Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Olmstead, R. G. (2013) Investigating the evolution of Lantaneae (Verbenaceae) using multiple loci. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 171: 103 - 119. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.2012.01305. x" type="journal article" year="2013">Lu-Irving &amp; Olmstead 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
